The Vice President of the United States spoke with Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe about various topics. They welcomed Japan's new policy on collective self-defense, which will strengthen the U.S.-Japan alliance and contribute to peace and security globally. They also discussed Japan's sanctions on Russia and the importance of G-7 coordination to pressure Russia to cease its destabilizing actions in Ukraine. The Vice President expressed gratitude for Japan's support in achieving a peaceful solution to Iran's nuclear program and agreed to continue coordinating on the issue. They emphasized the need for close coordination on North Korea and discussed supporting countries dealing with instability from conflicts in Iraq and Syria, particularly Jordan. The Vice President also appreciated Japan's engagement in Latin America and the Caribbean.